{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01BBzJsdJs1Yh9uFnjbvywZH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The original (`last-applied`) used `ray://ray-head:10001` — that's the \"wrong head address\" (Ray Client mode, and port 10001 isn't even exposed by the service). It was already changed to `ray-head:6379`, but that still fails because the `ray-client` pod isn't a cluster node, so the driver can't attach. I'll put the self-contained join logic into the ConfigMap and recreate the pod."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1240,"cache_read_input_tokens":37948,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1240},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8d1ba73-3dc0-4c9c-84ca-a90e168405fa","uuid":"41229ee7-526b-4a57-a162-3f05af0b851a","request_id":"req_011CcAVDBnUgevfLBz43bHFH"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01BBzJsdJs1Yh9uFnjbvywZH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FMwVjGHTMpL2ubQMNhh5ks","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat <<'YAML' > /tmp/cm.yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: ray-job-script\n  namespace: ray\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: job-script\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\n    bench.ray.cluster: ray\ndata:\n  job.py: |\n    \"\"\"Connect to the Ray cluster head at ray-head:6379 and print a health check.\n\n    The ray-client pod is not itself a member of the Ray cluster, so a plain\n    driver-mode ray.init() against the head's GCS cannot find a matching local\n    raylet. We first register a lightweight (0-CPU) local node pointed at\n    ray-head:6379, then attach the driver and print \"pong\".\n    \"\"\"\n    import socket\n    import subprocess\n    import sys\n\n    HEAD_ADDR = \"ray-head:6379\"\n\n\n    def ensure_joined():\n        \"\"\"Join the Ray cluster as a lightweight node (idempotent).\"\"\"\n        node_ip = socket.gethostbyname(socket.gethostname())\n        subprocess.run(\n            [\"ray\", \"start\", \"--address\", HEAD_ADDR,\n             \"--node-ip-address\", node_ip, \"--num-cpus\", \"0\"],\n            check=False,\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n        )\n\n\n    def main():\n        ensure_joined()\n        import ray\n        ray.init(address=HEAD_ADDR, logging_level=\"error\")\n        try:\n            print(\"pong\")\n        finally:\n            ray.shutdown()\n        subprocess.run([\"ray\", \"stop\"], check=False,\n                       stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL)\n\n\n    if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n        sys.exit(main())\nYAML\nkubectl apply -f /tmp/cm.yaml","description":"Update ray-job-script ConfigMap"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1240,"cache_read_input_tokens":37948,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1240},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8d1ba73-3dc0-4c9c-84ca-a90e168405fa","uuid":"24e056ab-3837-4c26-a584-53369b7b2aaa","request_id":"req_011CcAVDBnUgevfLBz43bHFH"}
