{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01P8Z5XyyGaCUvHYPtPEG661","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The task is complete and verified.\n\n## What was wrong\n- `/opt/job.py` is a **read-only `subPath` mount** from ConfigMap `ray-job-script`, so the file can't be edited in the pod directly.\n- The original script connected with `ray://ray-head:10001` (Ray Client mode) — the wrong address, and port 10001 isn't even exposed by the `ray-head` service (only `6379` GCS and `8265` dashboard).\n- Simply switching to `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` still failed: the `ray-client` pod is **not a member of the Ray cluster**, so a driver-mode `ray.init` against the head's GCS can't find a matching local raylet (`...none of these match this node's IP...`).\n\n## Fix\nUpdated the `ray-job-script` ConfigMap so the job:\n1. Registers the client pod as a lightweight (0-CPU) node against `ray-head:6379` (`ray start --address ray-head:6379`), idempotently.\n2. Attaches the driver via `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")`, prints `pong`, then cleans up.\n\nThen recreated the `ray-client` pod (required because `subPath` ConfigMap mounts don't hot-reload).\n\n## Verification\n```\nkubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- python /opt/job.py\n→ pong\nEXIT:0\n```\nConfirmed exit 0 + `pong`, and verified it's repeatable on a second run."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":330,"cache_read_input_tokens":42550,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":330},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8d1ba73-3dc0-4c9c-84ca-a90e168405fa","uuid":"eff70e4e-ab82-4eb1-9e39-8da059115f0f","request_id":"req_011CcAVTt9W5k8QaXZ3iVMkR"}
